cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use SENTINEL in your research or reference its governance design, please cite the accompanying paper and this software artifact."
type: software
title: "SENTINEL: AI Reasoning Observatory for MCP Agent Governance"
abstract: >
  SENTINEL is an MCP-native governance layer for AI agents. It audits the
  reasoning that underlies pending agent decisions --- scoring signal
  fidelity (was the evidence complete and current?), matching known failure
  signatures, computing historical reliability, and assigning an authority
  tier (FULL_AUTO, ACT_AND_NOTIFY, HUMAN_REQUIRED, QUARANTINE) --- before
  irreversible actions commit. It is deployed behind agentgateway and
  exposes four MCP tools (sentinel_evaluate, sentinel_reliability,
  sentinel_patterns, sentinel_pull_decisions) usable by any MCP client.
  This repository is the MCP-native reference implementation of the
  mid-reasoning interception framework described in the companion paper,
  "SENTINEL: A Mid-Reasoning Interception Framework for Auditing Medical
  AI Agents in Production."
